cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper investigates the QoE of users running real-life real-time and delay-tolerant applications by implementing an Internet-connected real-world mobile network. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the optimal resource allocation for bandwidth utilization in communications systems, which is a key concept in information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions specific traffic types with specific QoS requirements, which are often associated with multimedia applications. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses a centralized convex resource allocation optimization algorithm to calculate and enforce an optimal bandwidth distribution, which is a control system concept. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not a major focus of the paper, the concept of resource allocation optimization can also be applied to security and cryptography systems.
